text: Came in today. Got a little lost, so it's in the corner of valley view and Ali baba FYI. Place is very nice. Needs a remodeling a little inside. I ask our server and told me they've only been open for 3 months! They will don't have their alcohol license and were out of couple things we had order. Yet the server was very kind and he explained us that they make everything fresh for the week. So maybe I'll try coming in the weekend next time! Loved the food, I had a beef empanada and it was delightful, my sister had a cucumber and tomato salad, to our taste was missing lemon flavor but that's an easy fix (just ask for lemons) drinks are very originals and lastly the server brought us on the house dessert we tried alfajor and brownies with manjar!!! The only reason why it doesn't have 5 stars it's because of the items not being available and the liquor license. But I loved service and the atmosphere. Mostly the food. I work near by so I will be coming back to have lunch here again for sure

Great food, great service, friendly staff, fair prices. What else could you ask for! Oh, the desserts are to die for!! Also love the vegetarian options!! The veggie and spinach empanadas are delicious!

I have a love/hate relationship with this place: I love them when I can get to them, I hate that they're only open weekdays. Unless I am off work, I literally cannot come here. Which is a shame, because their empanadas are great and I have been wanting to try their lomito sandwich and other items. 

The empanadas are available in chicken, beef, ham and cheese, corn, mushroom and blue cheese, and vegetable varieties- and so far the mushroom version is my favorite, and freshly made to order. Buy way more than you think you'll need because once you try them, you won't want to share. Anxious for summer break to get here so I can pop by regularly and try more of the menu!
Really friendly staff. The owner is usually there and is a really nice guy. They have great food and their empanadas are the best I've had, Highly recommend trying them all around great atmosphere

New ownership has it advantages! A spin with a new menu and still keeping some of the oldies! Like Ravioli in a Pink Sauce.... . 

Really good spot for business lunches. Enjoy!
Quiet but good the empanada were fresh and delicious. My husband is very picky Cuban and he loves them.

This place is a real jewel, hidden in an industrial area just off of Valley View near the Strip in Las Vegas.

We saw a sign for Gyros and Argentinian food and had to stop, and we came into this place to be greeted by amazing smells of cooking and a friendly couple who own and run this wonderful hybrid place.

The chicken kabobs are laid out on a bed of rice with perfect seasoning, along with grilled onions and peppers, and the portions are huge. My wife had the beef kabobs, and the empanadas and fell in love.

They have spinach and blue cheese, and a variety of flavors and if you're lucky you'll come in on a day when they have a daily special of white fish in sauce...

Try the little cupcake sized quiche looking things called casanidas (I think) which are warm, gooey and wonderful.

We have offices across the street and now dine here on a regular basis or get take-out...either way we lucked out when we moved into this area.

Owner Pablo takes great care of his customers. The homemade chimichurri is excellent. The empanadas are authentic. Plenty of vegetarian options. This is a great authentic local spot, away from the fake tourist traps.
Loved the empanadas, fillings were delicious and crust was light and crispy.  Also had the schwarma plate which I enjoyed too but wished they had lamb instead of chicken.

Después de Maru's Restaurant , está son las mejores empanadas que comí aquí em Las Vegas, también los sándwich de miga tostadas de jamón y queso excelentes, todo lo que probé está muy bueno, inclusive los flanes también. Voy a seguir viniendo para probar las especiales que tienen a diario que según mi amigo Gregory el Bombero están excelentes. Espero que pronto sirvan vino  y cerveza . Los felicito y les agradezco por tanto esfuerzo...

husband is from Argentina so of course we came here one night on our way home. He saw Argentina something next thing i know i was on their parking lot lol.
Hidden cute place.
they have a nice selection of Argentinian dish on their menu.
we ordered all the empanadas on their menu to try.
they are fresh, home made and so so good.
we ordered a total of 20 and had to wait 30mns for them to make and bake it.

will come next time and try what's on the menu.
they are very busy during lunch time specially with all the businesses surrounding  them.

The food was really good! The empanadas were perfectly baked, the chimichurri was delicious with a little kick to it, and the crepes with dulce de leche were a sweet finish. Everything was made in house and the server was very personable. I'd give it a 5, but service is a little slow so this is more for when you can sit down and relax. We'll be back!

Saw this restaurant at Ali Baba and Valley View and the sign said serving Shawarma & Falafal, so I had to stop in!! I'm glad I did. Made in Argentina is really really good. I had the (Chicken Empanada's) little half moon hand held meat pies and there are many different fillings to chose from including:  beef, chicken, spinach, blue cheese, onions, ham & cheese, veggie, mushrooms & corn. Of course my eyes were bigger than my stomach so I ordered the (Shawarma Plate) and this dish is a must try for anyone who loves Middle Eastern food. From the super smooth and creamy humus, to the super fresh chopped tomatoes, cucumbers and fresh basmati rice to the perfectly cooked and crisped chicken bits and don't let me forget the warm and fresh pita bread, this dish is a world class home run!!!

The owner is working and serving food along with the other pleasant and knowledgeable staff. The restaurant is inviting and super clean. I will definitely be back.
Excellent food and very friendly service. Great casual atmosphere. If you are a meat lover like me, Try The Milanesa Beef or Lomitos Sandwich!

This is my favorite place to eat my lunch, very friendly staff and service the location it's very convenient like a few blocks from the strip and the best Part the amazing food they have like the best empanadas ever the chimichurry sauce it's addictive the milanesa it's very tasty  fresh meat and a lot of variety of delicious food , thx Made in Argentina

I definitely recommend coming to this restaurant.The owner Pablo greeted us, and attended to our every need. A wonderful mixture of Argentina fare and Greek food. After ordering five items off the menu, Pablo brought us a complimentary flan dessert. Thank goodness he did! It was epic. Try the empanadas. Such a light flaky crust, and really inexpensive. $2.10. Try the pickled eggplant too. The complimentary herb dressing is divine! We are extremely happy!

My lunch specials for a 4.99 hamburger went to 8.30 with the addition of a can of diet coke and tax. Most expensive diet coke off the strip. Glad I didn't buy a 7.99 shawarma wrap it might have cost me 10 or 12 bucks.
This place is great. Our office is conveniently around the corner from them and we typically go here for empanadas every week. The food is excellent and the service is usually the same.
This place is awesome, food is delicious, staff is always friendly, and prices are good. Can't ask for more. It's a little piece os Argentina in Vegas!!

Today I went to have lunch with my family, I ordered chicken and beef empanadas... They were absolutely delicious and sooo juicy. The owner is a sweetheart and his staff gives world class service. Very cozy family oriented and comfortable spot. I recommend this place 100%. Their prices are very reasonable and their meats are top quality. I am definitely coming back.

This restaurant offers everything from hamburgers, breakfast fare including quiches, raviolis, Mediterranean fare and pizza, but we stopped by for the empanadas.  Our friendly server Lao, short for Leonardo, explained the options and mentioned that all but the chicken and beef were deep fried.  We went with his favorite of beef plus a chicken.  While we waited, we received toasted bread with a delicious, addicting chimichurri sauce.  The empanadas were delicious so we will likely be returning soon.
Authentic Argentinean restaurant, great for breakfast and lunch! Delicious coffee and pastries, paired with a sense of pride. Lunch choices are traditional as well. Highly recommend
Hidden spot. Very good food, very good service. Be prepared for a flavor explosion in your mouth.

This place is amazing and Im so glad I found it. The empanadas are just delicious, the beef ones are tasty, try the spinach ones also they are to die for. Milhojas cake and panqueques with dulce de leche for dessert!!
Now they have medialunas !! A typical pastry from Argentina it was amazing. This place rocks!

Excellent food and warm service.  Best empanadas that I had so far in LV.  They were larger than the other Argentine place and tastier.  The chimichurri had a nice kick.  The choripan reminded me of Argentina as a child.  We had the mil ojas for desert and it was excellent as well.  The owner gave us a warm welcome.  The waitress was equally friendly.  Nice down to earth place for a family friendly meal.  Nice expansion to the side with larger private area for parties. The owner said is expanding to serve parrillada soon, looking forward to it in our next visit! Gracias mi amigo!

My wife had the muffin quiche and she thinks it  was out of this world!

Always on the lookout for new food options I was thrilled to find this spot. It's kind of hard to get to if you don't work in the area and have a regular 9-5 like me but luckily I was off one day and made the trek for lunch. 

Tasty empanadas that come in many varieties, I stocked up on one of each so I could take some home and enjoy them later as well. 

Friendly service and homemade Argentinian treats, what's not to like.
